# NPM Configuration for Private Maroon Studios Repositories
# 
# IMPORTANT: This is an example file. Copy this to .npmrc and replace placeholders with actual values.
# NEVER commit the actual .npmrc file with credentials to version control.
#
# For SSH-based authentication (recommended):
# 1. Generate SSH key: ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "your_email@example.com"
# 2. Add public key to your Maroon Studios account
# 3. Test connection: ssh -T git@repo.maroonstudios.com
#
# For HTTPS-based authentication (alternative):
# Uncomment and configure the following if using HTTPS with token:
# //repo.maroonstudios.com/:_authToken=${MAROON_STUDIOS_TOKEN}
#
# For CI/CD environments:
# Set MAROON_STUDIOS_TOKEN as an environment variable in your CI/CD pipeline
# The token should be stored in AWS Secrets Manager or similar secure storage
